program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make energy efficiency improvements, with the purchase and installation of a more efficient chiller system, at a dairy located near Elkton, South Dakota. This project will save $16,782.07 per year in energy costs and will save 282,890 kilowatt hours (kWh) of electricity per year (68.35 percent) which is enough electricity to power 26 homes. The purpose of this funding program is to assist farmers, ranchers, and rural small businesses in developing renewable energy systems, and in making energy-efficiency improvements to their operations.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for purchase and installation of an energy efficient printing press system (1000BE). This project will realize $95,538.00 per year in savings, and is estimated to replace 1,817,542 kilowatt hours (kWh) per year (51.18 percent), which is enough electricity to power 167 homes. The purpose of this funding program is to assist farmers, ranchers, and rural small businesses in developing renewable energy systems, and in making energy-efficiency improvements to their operations.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make energy efficiency improvements, with the purchase and installation of a more efficient grain dryer, at a farm located near Conde, South Dakota. This project will save $6,087.14 per year in energy costs and will save 225,406 kilowatt hours (kWh) of electricity per year (55.23 percent) which is enough electricity to power 20 homes. The purpose of this funding program is to assist farmers, ranchers, and rural small businesses in developing renewable energy systems, and in making energy-efficiency improvements to their operations.

naics_description: RESCUE AND AMBULANCE SERVICE - EQUIPMENT BUILDING
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist the Vale Fire Department in purchasing search and rescue suits and an extrication tool. The search and rescue clothing will serve as a protective barrier for the search and rescue team, while the extrication tool will aid in emergency situations in which extraction of people from cars or dwellings proves difficult. The Fire Department operates out of Vale, S.D. hosting a rural population of 136 people.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make energy efficiency improvements, with the purchase and installation of a more efficient grain dryer, at a farm located near Pierpont, South Dakota. This project will save $34,567.20 per year in energy costs and will save 876,095 kilowatt hours (kWh) of electricity per year (75.14 percent) which is enough electricity to power 80 homes. The purpose of this funding program is to assist farmers, ranchers, and rural small businesses in developing renewable energy systems, and in making energy-efficiency improvements to their operations.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make energy efficiency improvements, with the purchase and installation of more efficient grain handling equipment, at a farm located near New Effington, South Dakota. This project will save $884.45 per year in energy costs and will save 21,832 kilowatt hours (kWh) of electricity per year (89.32 percent) which is enough electricity to power two homes. The purpose of this funding program is to assist farmers, ranchers, and rural small businesses in developing renewable energy systems, and in making energy-efficiency improvements to their operations.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional financing for improvements to the City of Redfields water distribution system. Redfield will add a SCADA system to the current booster station and replace outdated distribution lines throughout the community. These improvements will create operating efficiencies and provide a reliable water distribution system for the communitys residents. Total project cost is $8,172,000. Local funds will be used in conjunction with Rural Development funding in order to complete the enhancements and provide a more efficient water distribution system for this rural South Dakota community.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide funding forworking capital and is made available to agricultural producers seeking to establish or expand markets for their value-added agricultural products. funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to cover the cost that Huron Regional Medical Center incurred during the COVID-19 pandemic. Funds will also be used to purchase new equipment to help with current and future health care needs of Beadle County. The funds will reimburse them for many expenses incurred during the height of the pandemic from intubation pods to noninvasive ventilators. Beadle County was one of South Dakotas first hot spots. Huron Regional Medical Centers decisive actions helped get the pandemic under control in a county with diverse communities and meat processing facilities. This grant will also allow Huron Regional Medical Center to upgrade neonate ventilators and equipment to store vaccines and prepare the hospital for any surges from future pandemics.

Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to finance the expansion and renovations of the Bennett County Hospital. Original construction of the hospital was completed in 1954 and no longer meets disabled accessibility standards or modern practices in health care.This project will help to remodel nearly 8,000 square feet of the existing space and remove 4,000 square feet to allow for new construction of a 15,000 square foot addition.The new construction will include an expanded emergency room area and entrance, create 15 private rooms (eliminating existing shared rooms), and expand imaging space.The hospitals heating, ventilations and air conditioning, fire suppression, and medical gas systems will also be replaced.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase health care equipment to help address the varying needs of rural residents in the wake of the COVID-19 pandemic. Equipment purchases include two new ambulances, two home health care vehicles, a portable X-ray machine, ultrasound machine, three temperature screening kiosks and an ultraviolet sterilizer. The updates will allow Bennett County Hospital to be better equipped to handle future pandemics and treat more patients locally. Home Health vehicles will allow hospital staff to extend services to residents who are unable to travel in Bennett, Oglala Lakota, Jackson, and Todd counties.

Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional funding to alleviate major water treatment plant inadequacies within the city of Springfield. Funds will be used to construct a water treatment plant to replace the citys current facility, which was constructed in 1966. The plant will have the capacity to withdraw water at 460 gallons per minute from the Missouri River. Plant equipment will be housed in a 60 by 100 structure, just west of the current facility, which will be taken down once construction of the facility is complete. This project also will consist of constructing a same size water intake system parallel to the current intake line. This project will benefit 746 rural users.

naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install a more efficient heater, doors, lights, and skylights, at an equine boarding facility located near Aberdeen, South Dakota. This project will save $3,543.09 per year in energy costs and will save 34,313 kilowatt hours (kWh) of electricity per year (56.12 percent) which is enough electricity to power three homes.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Sumption Farms purchase and install an energy efficient grain dryer near Frederick, South Dakota. naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a computerized topography (CT) scanner, vaccine refrigerator and freezer, and heating, ventilation, and air conditioning (HVAC) system. This equipment will allow Wagner Community Memorial Hospital to offer quality services in rural areas. During the COVID-19 pandemic the CT scanner usage increased significantly, which decreased its useful life. The hospital also is updating their vaccine storage equipment, which is important for their service area and other service areas, as the Wagner Community Memorial Hospital is a distribution point for other clinics in Charles Mix County. The new HVAC system will provide heating and cooling to all areas of the hospital, further mitigating the spread of viruses and bacteria.

naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: RESCUE AND AMBULANCE SERVICE - EQUIPMENT BUILDING
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase ambulances and equipment from the current privately owned ambulance service, whose owners are retiring. Day County does not have another ambulance service, nor were any of the surrounding counties able to provide the needed services, which would leave Day County residents with a huge gap in their emergency service care. The applicant will use the funds to purchase the equipment portion of the current ambulance service. The grant will also allow Day County to upgrade two ambulances and purchase an automated chest compression system. Ambulance services are a necessity during normal times, but the pandemic created even more urgency. As a front-line provider, it is imperative they be able to reach and stabilize patients in their service area.

Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to stabilize a landslide that is occurring near the Mni Waste Water Company water intake source. Should the landslide progress, it could jeopardize the sole source of water for the entire system. Extensive dirt work, rock buttresses, and stabilization mats will be implemented to prevent further land slide activity. Rural Development funding consists of $950,000 while the South Dakota Department of Agriculture & Natural Resources has contributed $1,238,302. In addition, the Water Company has secured $770,000 in Community Development Block Grant funds. This project will ensure continued access to drinking water for the estimated 7,433 rural residents of the water system.

naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
naics_description: RESCUE AND AMBULANCE SERVICE - EQUIPMENT BUILDING
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to upgrade ambulances. A power load system will be added to both ambulances, enabling staff to move patients quickly and safely. The older ambulances chassis will be replaced, allowing the city of Freeman to improve their ability to reach and transport patients during inclement weather. The COVID pandemic strained many small communities health care providers and equipment. Many common items had surge a in usage, therefore creating a need to upgrade or replace equipment sooner than anticipated. Ambulances were not exempt from this issue. As a front-line provider, it is imperative they be able to reach and stabilize patients in their service area.

program: Meat and Poultry Intermediary Lending Program (MPILP)
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: District III will establish a financial resource that builds District IIIs lending capacity while focusing on a chronic economic challenge, namely creating value added agricultural alternatives. The fund will give local processing facilities a tool to improve access to markets; enhance operational efficiencies; retain and attract employees; and remain competitive in a challenging business environment.

borrower_name: LEWIS AND CLARK BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES INC.
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a facility for Lewis and Clark Behavioral Health Services Inc. Established in 1977 to provide behavioral health and substance abuse services, they have been operating out of several buildings located at different sites throughout Yankton, South Dakota. The new project will help to improve safety, care and accessibility for patients and staff by housing all services under one roof. The new facility will be located in Yankton and provide services to Yankton, Bon Homme, Charles Mix, Clay, Gregory, Hutchinson, Union, Yankton, Douglas, Davison, Aurora, Brule, Jerauld, Miner, Sanborn, Hanson, Buffalo, Lyman, and Tripp counties.

program: Rural Economic Development Loan and Grant (REDLG)
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to relocate and renovate Huron Regional Medical Centers (HRMC) dialysis program. Dakota Energy Cooperatives subsequent revolving loan will provide funding for a new water filtration system, while renovations will expand the unit from seven to twelve treatment chairs in the dialysis treatment center. The project will expand dialysis services to the residents of seven rural counties in South Dakota. Critical access hospitals are the cornerstone of rural health care systems, contributing to the health and wellness of local residents, and the overall economic strength of the community.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional financingto WEB Water Development Association (WEB) to complete its water treatment plant expansion project. WEB is expanding the water treatment plant to provide adequate water capacity to its service area. WEB will construct two new raw water regulating tanks, add a clearwell structure, replace their two remaining original high service pumps, add a fifth high service pump and construct an additional wash-water recovery basin. These improvements, totaling $39,400,000, are critical to serving the needs of their system.

program: Meat and Poultry Intermediary Lending Program (MPILP)
naics_industry_sector: Other Services (except Public Administration) (81)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to capitalize South Dakotas Planning & Development District IIIs "Regional Meat and Poultry Revolving Fund". The fund is being established to targeted financial assistance to build capacity and resiliency in the agricultural processing sector. The fund will give local processing facilities a tool to improve access to markets; enhance operational efficiencies; retain and attract employees; and remain competitive in a challenging business environment. Meat and Poultry Intermediary Lending Program (MPILP) offers an opportunity to support and establish a financial resource that builds District IIIs lending capacity while focusing on creating value added agricultural alternatives.

borrower_name: LEWIS AND CLARK BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES INC.
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional funding for the construction of the new Lewis and Cark Behavioral Health Services (LCBHS) facility. LCBHS was established in 1977 to provide behavioral health and substance abuse services, and has been operating out of several buildings located at different sites throughout Yankton, South Dakota. The new facility will house all services in a 59,616 sq foot building and provide safe, private and high level of care.
